The Sunday Times is reporting today, that Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane, has widened her probe into President Cyril Ramaphosa's campaign funds. JOHANNESBURG - The Sunday Times is reported on the weekend that Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane has widened her probe into President Cyril Ramaphosa's campaign funds. READ: Ramaphosa obliged to respond to Mkhwebane's Bosasa report Mkhwebane has been investigating DA leader Mmusi Maimane's complaint,
about Bosasa's R500,000 donation towards Ramaphosa's ANC presidential campaign. It has emerged she is also looking at other funds to the tune of R4-million and possible money-laundering. READ: Ramaphosa investigated by Public Protector Sunday Times journalist Quaanita Hunter said the outcome of the investigation could have serious implications for the president. "There are no rules when it comes to campaign fundraising in South Africa," Hunter said. She explained her sources stated the people who donated to the campaign were kept anonymous so there were no conflicts of interest.